OpenID authentication for the Ada Web Server library (AWS).

Build (with demo application):

   SERVER_NAME=your.server.name ./configure && make

Run demo application:

   sudo ./demo/openid_demo

We start with a branch of "Ada Server Faces" which means that the code in 
this repository for the time being is under the Apache 2 license. 
This is compatible with GPL-3 (but apparently not with GPL-2), so 
applications compiled with this will end up being either Apache-2 or 
GPL-3 licensed.

